3. Complete characterization of the Optimal Switching Frontier (Theorem 7.1) as the rate-distortion curve of the information bottleneck, with threshold policies achieving Pareto optimality.
4. Benchmark design principles for theoretical evaluation, guiding the interpretation of results and the choice of assumptions.

These lemmas and metrics unify the mathematical developments of the preceding chapters into a coherent framework for analyzing and optimizing dual-cognitive architectures.

